DURING A TAKE OFF, THE AIRCRAFT WAS OBSERVED IN A NOSE HIGH ATTITUDE. AFTER 
REACHING AN ALTITUDE OF ABOUT 300 FEET AGL, IT WENT INTO A STEEP DSCNT AND 
CRASHED IN ABOUT A 70 DEG NOSE LOW ATTITUDE. NO PREIMPACT PART FAILURE 
OR MALFUNCTION WAS EVIDENT. REPORTEDLY, THE PILOT WAS MAKING A TOUCH-AND-
GO LANDING WHEN THE ACCIDENT OCCURRED. DURING THE PREVIOUS 90 DAYS, 
THE PILOT HAD FLOWN ONLY ONCE WHEN HE MADE 3 TAKEOFFS AND LANDINGS ON A .5 
HR FLIGHT ON 9/20/86. 
